cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.CV, cs.CL

The paper introduces a quantitative evaluation method based on learning, which involves designing a neural network model to fit an evaluation function. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI and cs.LG, which deal with artificial intelligence and machine learning. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the deciding factors of MOBA game results, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.GT, which deals with game theory. The paper also applies its method to Defense of the Ancients 2 (DotA2), which is a video game, suggesting that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.CV and cs.CL, which deal with computer vision and natural language processing, respectively.
